\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 11. Preferences
\f0\b0\fs24 \
Open Preferences with Jedit > Preferences (
\f2 \uc0\u8984 
\f0 ,). Preferences are organized into the following tabs:\
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 General Preferences
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab640\li360\fi-360\slleading200\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \'95 Appearance \'97 Choose between System Default, Light, or Dark appearance mode.\
\'95 Startup \'97 Configure what happens when Jedit launches: create a new document, show the Open dialog, or restore previously open documents.\
\'95 Auto-start \'97 Option to launch Jedit at system login.\
\'95 Date Format \'97 Choose from predefined date formats or create a custom format for the Insert > Date command.\
\'95 Time Format \'97 Choose from predefined time formats or create a custom format for the Insert > Time command.\
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 New Documents Preferences
\f0\b0\fs24 \
Configure the default settings for newly created documents:\
\pard\pardeftab640\li360\fi-360\slleading200\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \'95 Default Preset \'97 Select which preset to use for the 
\f2 \uc0\u8984 
\f0 N shortcut.\
\'95 Document Naming \'97 Choose the naming format for untitled documents: sequential number, timestamp, date with serial, locale-aware date, etc.\
\'95 Default Encoding \'97 Set the default character encoding for new plain text documents.\
\'95 Default Line Endings \'97 Set the default line ending style.\
\'95 Font \'97 Set the default font and size for new documents.\
\'95 Colors \'97 Set the default text and background colors.\
\'95 Page Layout \'97 Set default margins, paper size, and orientation.\
\'95 Headers/Footers \'97 Configure default header and footer content for printing.\
\'95 View Settings \'97 Set default toolbar, ruler, line number, zoom, and other display options.\
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Encodings Preferences
\f0\b0\fs24 \
Customize the list of character encodings shown in encoding popup menus throughout Jedit. You can enable or disable individual encodings and reorder them. Click "Revert to Default" to restore the default encoding list.\

\f1\b\fs28 Line Breaking Preferences
\f0\b0\fs24 \
Configure Japanese typographic line-breaking rules (Kinsoku Shori). These rules control where line breaks can and cannot occur:\
\pard\pardeftab640\li360\fi-360\slleading200\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \'95 Line-start prohibited characters \'97 Characters that must not appear at the beginning of a line (e.g., closing brackets, punctuation).\
\'95 Line-end prohibited characters \'97 Characters that must not appear at the end of a line (e.g., opening brackets).\
\'95 Hanging characters (Burasagari) \'97 Characters that are allowed to extend beyond the right margin.\
\'95 Non-separable characters \'97 Character pairs that must not be split across lines.\
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Choose from preset rules (Simple, Standard, Strict) or customize individual character sets.\
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

