\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 13. Encoding and Line Endings
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Supported Encodings
\f0\b0\fs24 \
Jedit supports a wide range of character encodings, including:\
\pard\pardeftab640\li360\fi-360\slleading200\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \'95 Unicode: UTF-8, UTF-16 (Big Endian, Little Endian), UTF-32\
\'95 Japanese: Shift-JIS, EUC-JP, ISO-2022-JP, Mac Japanese\
\'95 Western: Mac Roman, Windows Latin-1, ISO Latin-1, ASCII\
\'95 Chinese: Mac Chinese Traditional, Mac Chinese Simplified, GB-18030\
\'95 Korean: Mac Korean\
\'95 And many more via the macOS text encoding system\
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Automatic Encoding Detection
\f0\b0\fs24 \
When opening a plain text file, Jedit uses a sophisticated multi-step detection process:\
\pard\pardeftab640\li360\fi-360\slleading200\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \'95 1. BOM Detection \'97 Checks for byte order marks at the start of the file.\
\'95 2. Extended Attribute \'97 Reads the com.apple.TextEncoding attribute if present.\
\'95 3. Content Analysis \'97 Analyzes byte patterns to determine the encoding with a confidence score.\
\'95 4. User Selection \'97 If confidence is low, prompts you to choose.\
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0
\cf0 The encoding is displayed in the toolbar and can be changed at any time.\
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Line Endings
\f0\b0\fs24 \
Jedit supports three line ending styles:\
\pard\pardeftab640\li360\fi-360\slleading200\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \'95 LF (Line Feed, \\n) \'97 Unix, macOS, and Linux standard.\
\'95 CR (Carriage Return, \\r) \'97 Classic Mac OS standard.\
\'95 CRLF (CR+LF, \\r\\n) \'97 Windows standard.\
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0
\cf0 When opening a file, Jedit automatically detects the line ending style by counting occurrences of each type and using the most frequent. You can change the line ending style using the toolbar popup or when saving.\
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Byte Order Mark (BOM)
\f0\b0\fs24 \
A BOM is an optional marker at the start of a Unicode text file that identifies the encoding. You can choose to include or exclude a BOM when saving Unicode files. The BOM option is available for UTF-8, UTF-16, and UTF-32 encodings.\

\f1\b\fs28 Special Character Conversions
\f0\b0\fs24 \
Jedit supports special character conversion options for Japanese text:\
\pard\pardeftab640\li360\fi-360\slleading200\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \'95 Yen Sign (\'a5) 
\f4 \uc0\u8596 
\f0  Backslash (\\) conversion \'97 Handle the classic Japanese encoding ambiguity.\
\'95 Overline (\uc0\u8254 ) 
\f4 \uc0\u8596 
\f0  Tilde (~) conversion\
\'95 Full-width Tilde conversion\
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

\fs2 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 14. AppleScript Support
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Scripts Menu
\f0\b0\fs24 \
Jedit includes a Scripts menu that provides access to AppleScript files. Scripts are loaded from ~/Library/Application Scripts/. On first launch, Jedit installs sample scripts demonstrating common automation tasks.\
To add your own scripts, place .scpt, .applescript, or .scptd files in the Application Scripts folder. They will appear in the Scripts menu automatically.\

\f1\b\fs28 Scripting Commands
\f0\b0\fs24 \
Jedit's AppleScript dictionary (accessible via Script Editor > Open Dictionary) supports the following commands:\
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 Standard Suite
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab640\li360\fi-360\slleading200\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \'95 open \'97 Open a document\
\'95 close \'97 Close a document\
\'95 save \'97 Save a document\
\'95 print \'97 Print a document (with options for copies, collating, pages)\
\'95 quit \'97 Quit the application\
\'95 count \'97 Count objects (characters, words, paragraphs)\
\'95 delete \'97 Delete text\
\'95 duplicate \'97 Duplicate objects\
\'95 exists \'97 Check if an object exists\
\'95 make \'97 Create new objects\
\'95 move \'97 Move objects\
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 Jedit-Specific Commands
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab640\li360\fi-360\slleading200\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \'95 find \'97 Search for text in a document\
\'95 insert \'97 Insert text at the current selection\
\'95 select \'97 Select a range of text\
\'95 replace \'97 Find and replace text\
\'95 begin undo group \'97 Start grouping multiple actions as a single undo step\
\'95 end undo group \'97 End the undo group\
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Document Properties via Script
\f0\b0\fs24 \
AppleScript can access and modify document properties including text content, selection, font settings, formatting, and metadata (author, title, keywords, etc.).\
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

\fs2 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 15. Markdown Support
\f0\b0\fs24 \
Jedit includes built-in Markdown support, providing both rendering and export capabilities.\
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Supported Markdown Syntax
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 Block Elements
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab640\li360\fi-360\slleading200\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \'95 Headings \'97 # H1, ## H2, ### H3, #### H4, ##### H5, ###### H6\
\'95 Paragraphs \'97 Separated by blank lines\
\'95 Code Blocks \'97 Indented by 4 spaces or fenced with ``` (triple backticks)\
\'95 Block Quotes \'97 Lines starting with >\
\'95 Unordered Lists \'97 Lines starting with *, -, or +\
\'95 Ordered Lists \'97 Lines starting with numbers (1., 2., etc.)\
\'95 Horizontal Rules \'97 Three or more -, *, or _\
\'95 Tables \'97 With header rows and alignment separators\
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 Inline Elements
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab640\li360\fi-360\slleading200\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \'95 Bold \'97 **text** or __text__\
\'95 Italic \'97 *text* or _text_\
\'95 Bold Italic \'97 ***text*** or ___text___\
\'95 Inline Code \'97 `code`\
\'95 Links \'97 [text](url) or [text][reference]\
\'95 Strikethrough \'97 ~~text~~\
\'95 Subscript \'97 ~text~\
\'95 Superscript \'97 ^text^\
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Markdown Display
\f0\b0\fs24 \
When you open a Markdown (.md) file, Jedit renders the Markdown syntax as formatted rich text. Headings are displayed in larger fonts, bold and italic text is properly styled, code blocks use a monospace font with a background color, and lists are properly indented.\

\f1\b\fs28 Markdown Export
\f0\b0\fs24 \
You can export any document as Markdown by choosing Markdown (.md) in the Save As or Export dialog's format popup. Jedit converts the rich text formatting back to Markdown syntax, preserving headings, bold/italic, code blocks, lists, and other supported elements.\
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

\fs2 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab640\slleading200\partightenfactor0

